Befund solcher Darstellungsresistenz aus werden späte Erzähltexte Fontanes gelesen, vor allem »Die Poggenpuhls« und »Der Stechlin«. Unter Rückgriff auf ästhetische Elemente der frühen Photographie, auf die zeitgenössische Psychopathologie des Traumas und auf die romantische Poetik der Arabeske decken sie die Wahrnehmungsgrenzen der historistischen Geschichtskultur auf und entwerfen alternative Formen einer Textur der Historie.  aThe subject of this volume is historicist practice in the perception of history and the development that superseded it. Both Ranke and Droysen as well as Fontane in his texts on the war of 1870/71 assimilate their descriptive procedures to 19th-century public historical culture, which was based on a number of medial innovations. But by drawing upon the contemporary psychopathology of trauma, the romantic poetics of the arabesque and aesthetic elements in early photography, Fontane's late narratives indicate the limitations of this culture and map out a new texture of historiography.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aHistory in literature. 0aLiterature and historyzEuropexHistoryy19th century. 4aDroysen, Johann Gustav. 4aFontane, Theodor. 4aGeschichtsschreibung. 4aHistorismus. 4aRanke, Leopold, von. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / German.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Literary and Cultural Studies 2000 - 2014z9783110637854oZDB-23-GLC0 cprintz978348415099740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311094614740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110946147423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110946147/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-GLCc2000d2014